com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day01
Extract the first and last digits (specified as digit characters or words) from each line of input and sum the resulting two-digit integers.
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day02
Filter a sequence of random drawings (read from an input file) of red, green, and blue balls by the feasibility of each, given a specified maximum number of each—as well as the smallest numbers of red, green, and blue balls which would make all of the drawings possible.
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day03
Identify and perform calculations on part numbers embedded in a schematic grid of characters (read from an input file), where part numbers are recognized by their adjacency to gears (represented by '*' characters) and other components.
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day04
Tabulate (and perform operations on) the matches between scratchcard picks and winning numbers, for a sequence of scratchcards read from an input file.
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day05
Translate seed numbers (read from an input file) to planting locations through a series of mapping operations (specified by input and output ranges read from the input).
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day06

com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day07
Rank a sequence of hands and wagers (read from an input file) for a simplified version of poker, and tabulate the winnings.
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day08
Count the number of steps required to traverse a single path between an initial node and a terminal node in a selected graph; then, compute the number of steps for multiple parallel traversals, all starting at the same time, and all ending on a terminal node at the same time (potentially after passing through one or more potential terminal nodes along the path).
com.nickbenn.adventofcode.day09
Extrapolate the next higher and next lower values for each of multiple sequences of input values, where each sequence is generated by some univariate polynomial expression.
